  <description>Stems ascending to erect, branched or unbranched, 0.4–3.3 dm, sparsely to moderately pubescent. Leaves: blade margins sinuate-dentate, shallowly pinnatifid, or entire, surfaces moderately pubescent. Flowers: petals white, pink, or purple, 2.5–6.9(–7.5) × (0.7–)0.9–4(–4.2) mm. Fruits usually fertile and fully developed, somewhat torulose, 0.6–1.2(–1.3) mm wide; septum not fenestrate or split longitudinally. 2n = 28, 42, 56, 70.</description>
